WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.320
There will be organizational beams.

2
00:00:02.560 --> 00:00:07.400
Internally, these beams are related to the lesser wing here.

3
00:00:07.640 --> 00:00:08.460
Beams here.

4
00:00:09.780 --> 00:00:12.380
You see, these are very important lines of force.

5
00:00:13.140 --> 00:00:17.000
But at the moment of primitive cephalic flexion,

6
00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:20.700
you will have the sub-mesencephalic mesenchyme

7
00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:24.660
which will compress between the anterior part of the brain vesicle

8
00:00:24.660 --> 00:00:27.000
and the posterior brain vesicle.

9
00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:27.940
This occurs initially.

10
00:00:28.070 --> 00:00:29.210
My tissue is like this.

11
00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:31.330
And through the flexion movement,

12
00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:33.670
it moves anteriorly.

13
00:00:34.410 --> 00:00:35.750
The underlying mesenchyme,

14
00:00:35.830 --> 00:00:37.870
will undergo a compression field along its axis.

15
00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:42.170
It will lose water,

16
00:00:42.530 --> 00:00:43.990
it will densify and become

17
00:00:43.990 --> 00:00:45.270
cartilaginous tissue.

18
00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:48.070
This is how the cranial base forms.

19
00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:50.150
Through the flexion movement.

20
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:52.770
Always with as its axis,

21
00:00:53.730 --> 00:00:54.410
my notochord.

22
00:00:54.670 --> 00:00:55.910
And on either side,

23
00:00:56.140 --> 00:01:01.200
We have, at the very top, what is called the ethmoid, just below

24
00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:03.060
the body of the sphenoid,

25
00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:06.960
even further below, the basilar part of the occipital bone,

26
00:01:07.240 --> 00:01:11.460
and especially here, what are called the sphenoid wings,

27
00:01:11.660 --> 00:01:14.680
but also the point where the eye will be situated.

28
00:01:16.140 --> 00:01:18.280
It is the support for the eye, the sphenoid.

29
00:01:18.460 --> 00:01:21.500
The sphenoid is very important for ocular stability.

30
00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.140
As it grows, the mesenchyme...

31
00:01:24.211 --> 00:01:25.791
which is superior, the bony capsule

32
00:01:26.531 --> 00:01:27.531
of the eye,

33
00:01:27.811 --> 00:01:30.251
will develop through the growth

34
00:01:30.251 --> 00:01:32.491
of the brain, around the eye.

35
00:01:33.531 --> 00:01:34.191
So the eye

36
00:01:34.191 --> 00:01:36.331
becomes there, it follows

37
00:01:36.331 --> 00:01:38.031
the movement, it is both conforming

38
00:01:38.031 --> 00:01:38.871
and conformed,

39
00:01:40.811 --> 00:01:42.391
and the osseous tissue

40
00:01:42.391 --> 00:01:44.371
comes to engram itself around, comes to close

41
00:01:44.371 --> 00:01:46.291
with specific lines of force

42
00:01:46.291 --> 00:01:48.291
that support the eye's position. This means that the eye

43
00:01:48.291 --> 00:01:50.091
can destabilize the cranium

44
00:01:50.091 --> 00:01:52.011
or the cranium can destabilize the eye.

45
00:01:52.281 --> 00:01:54.121
You see?

46
00:01:54.741 --> 00:01:55.721
A minor impact, a subtle perturbation

47
00:01:55.721 --> 00:01:58.261
can completely destabilize the orbit

48
00:01:58.261 --> 00:02:00.161
and completely destabilize

49
00:02:00.941 --> 00:02:02.421
the reflection, you see?

50
00:02:02.421 --> 00:02:03.761
Therefore, it is truly important to be able

51
00:02:03.761 --> 00:02:06.161
to restabilize the eye, to understand it

52
00:02:06.161 --> 00:02:08.221
both through the brain and through

53
00:02:08.221 --> 00:02:10.321
the cranium. This is your nose.

54
00:02:10.321 --> 00:02:12.241
It will grow.

55
00:02:13.161 --> 00:02:14.201
Boom! And there, we see the eye emerge

56
00:02:14.361 --> 00:02:16.061
laterally. And you see,

57
00:02:16.061 --> 00:02:18.081
simultaneously, the palatal system

58
00:02:18.161 --> 00:02:20.181
is forming. At the moment my

59
00:02:20.351 --> 00:02:22.511
eye is forming,

60
00:02:22.511 --> 00:02:24.491
mon Åil qui se fait,

61
00:02:24.611 --> 00:02:26.431
my palate is forming.

62
00:02:26.831 --> 00:02:28.131
Do you see?

63
00:02:28.131 --> 00:02:30.171
Indeed, with the closure. The palatine bone,

64
00:02:30.171 --> 00:02:32.091
here, which is setting. And when my eye has

65
00:02:32.091 --> 00:02:34.151
completely regained its

66
00:02:34.151 --> 00:02:36.311
axis in its verticality,

67
00:02:36.411 --> 00:02:37.791
and its horizontality,

68
00:02:38.011 --> 00:02:39.811
the palate is formed.

69
00:02:40.271 --> 00:02:41.951
Thus, it is truly the terminal

70
00:02:41.951 --> 00:02:42.651
terminal

71
00:02:43.991 --> 00:02:46.331
and very important osseous point that is established.

72
00:02:46.571 --> 00:02:48.171
This represents a primary convergence.

73
00:02:48.422 --> 00:02:52.562
Here we observe, you see, the growth, the significance of this growth.

74
00:02:52.782 --> 00:02:55.262
And observe the cephalic portion.

75
00:02:55.602 --> 00:02:59.122
It is at the moment when this cephalic portion truly begins to grow

76
00:02:59.122 --> 00:03:01.802
that the eyes converge towards the midline.

77
00:03:01.902 --> 00:03:05.502
Observe carefully, with a fulcrum established at the Nasion.

78
00:03:09.362 --> 00:03:10.822
Now, observe the white portion.

79
00:03:15.182 --> 00:03:16.062
It grows.

80
00:03:17.572 --> 00:03:19.012
Now, it expands rapidly.

81
00:03:22.292 --> 00:03:24.432
The eyes return towards the midline.

82
00:03:30.292 --> 00:03:31.872
Did you see?

83
00:03:32.612 --> 00:03:34.552
We revisit this biodynamic process

84
00:03:34.552 --> 00:03:36.432
or this developmental morphogenesis.

85
00:03:39.952 --> 00:03:42.112
This immense growth

86
00:03:42.912 --> 00:03:44.412
which originates from here.

87
00:03:45.502 --> 00:03:48.022
which causes my eyes to converge centrally.

88
00:03:49.462 --> 00:03:54.182
Cortical development guides the eye into its definitive position.

89
00:03:54.462 --> 00:03:56.082
There will be two spirals.

90
00:03:57.202 --> 00:03:58.802
One spiral of the eye

91
00:04:00.342 --> 00:04:04.402
and a counter-osseous spiral.

92
00:04:06.302 --> 00:04:08.442
You see this in the shape of the sutures.

93
00:04:08.602 --> 00:04:12.522
If you look closely, you must study the orientation of this suture.

94
00:04:12.633 --> 00:04:16.133
And you see that this pre-maxilla is three-dimensional.

95
00:04:18.413 --> 00:04:19.453
You see, it does this.

96
00:04:20.253 --> 00:04:24.693
You see, it ascends, it descends, and it re-ascends.

97
00:04:24.913 --> 00:04:26.593
And it truly exhibits three-dimensionality.

98
00:04:26.933 --> 00:04:33.993
And indeed, you see that it forms, this specific shape, orbital, ocular.

